item.title: Endometriosis Awareness, a comic by Lily Williams
item.description: Back when Imgur did the big content update about what was allowed on our private storage, my entire repository of uploads was wiped out, including my public posts. Don't care about that. I'd saved everything important and most of it was nonsense. Except for this one. This is important to keep up. I posted it last decade I think and people have probably posted it since then but more relevant than ever due to the wave of medical ignorance spreading and reversal of the progress made towards doctors not disregarding the suffering and experiences of their female patients. https://lilywilliamsart.com/portfolio/my-endo-story/

item.title: Choose Kindness
item.description: I've noticed there's been a lot of posts in usersub from fellow imgurians who are struggling right now... Please remember that this time of year isn’t always a happy time for everyone. While the world is filled with holiday cheer, the reality is that for many of us, it’s a time of struggle, sadness, or feeling disconnected... https://imgur.com/gallery/to-whoever-needs-to-hear-ae9fen0 We often don’t know what others are going through...Everyone is carrying something, even if they’re not showing it. It’s so easy to assume that people are okay just because they seem fine on the outside, but the truth is we can never fully understand the weight of someone’s story...So let’s be gentle with each other. Let’s choose kindness and compassion, because sometimes, the person who looks like they have it all together is actually the one who needs it most. I just want to take a moment to remind you that you are seen. Your pain is valid, your emotions are valid, and it’s okay to not have everything figured out. Even when it feels like no one notices, even when it feels like you're all alone, even when it feels there's nothing left here for you in this world, the important thing to remember is that YOU ARE NOT DEFINED BY YOUR STRUGGLES, and you are not alone in how you feel. You are loved, even when it’s hard to feel that love within yourself.   I know it’s easy to feel forgotten or invisible, especially when things are tough, but there are people here who see you. There are people who care. And I am one of them, wishing you nothing but peace, comfort, and brighter days ahead... Please...Be gentle with yourself...Be kind to yourself. you're doing the best you can and thats enough.

So, instead of finding the one thing in here you don't like and commenting only on that, also comment about something you DID like. Balance the negativity. Love you long time.
